               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-170-person1669">
                  EDWARD 
                  HANDS
               <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1669" type="surname" value="HANDS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1669" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1669" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman of Saint Luke's. On the 20th of August I went into Crown-court, between four and five o'clock in the morning; I saw the prisoner coming along the court, and another person with him. The prisoner had three saddles on his right shoulder - I caught hold of him, and he immediately threw them down - I called a porter to assist me, and we took him to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-170-person1670">
                  THOMAS 
                  MORGAN
               <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1670" type="surname" value="MORGAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1670" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1670" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am foreman to Mr. Sealey; he is a <rs id="t18270913-170-viclabel967" type="occupation">livery stable-keeper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-170-victim1668 t18270913-170-viclabel967"></join>. On the 19th of August I locked up these saddles safe in his stables - I went to the Leaping Bar public-house, to sleep, and the next morning, when I went to the stable, I found the door open, and the watchman there. I then looked and found the first padlock broken off; the second stable was on a springlock, that was broken - the third stable had a padlock, and the staple of that was drawn out. I know these saddles to be my master's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-170-person1671">
                  JAMES 
                  MADDEN
               <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1671" type="surname" value="MADDEN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1671" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1671" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a porter. I was coming out of my door, and saw the prisoner in custody of the watchman; he told me to take up the saddles. I put them into my basket, and took them to the watch-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-170-person1672">
                  JOHN 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1672" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1672" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1672" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am watch-house keeper. I went to see where they had been taken from, and found two locks broken, and the staple of the other drawn.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-170-person1673">
                  THOMAS 
                  FARROW
               <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1673" type="surname" value="FARROW"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1673" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-170-person1673" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. My brother watchman called me to assist him, which I did.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was going up Golden-lane, about half-past four, and met a man, who looked like a groom; he asked me to take these saddles to Smithfield. Soon after I took them, he made off.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270913-170-verdict968" type="verdictDescription">
